// Accept + run: explicit `.close()` on a `LambdaPid` handle compiles,
// lowers, and runs without E_NOT_YET_IMPLEMENTED.
//
// `actor |x: i64| { println(x); }` produces `LambdaPid<i64, ()>`.
// `.send(42)` delivers the message; the explicit `.close()` in statement
// context invokes `hew_lambda_actor_release` (routed by
// `Place::LambdaActorHandle` in `lower_duplex_close`). Exit 0 proves
// the program ran to completion; stdout "42" proves the message was
// delivered before the handle was released.
//
// This fixture guards the blocker: before the fix, the checker accepted
// `.close()` and recorded `hew_duplex_close`, but the MIR producer had
// no arm for that symbol → `E_NOT_YET_IMPLEMENTED` at compile time.
fn main() {
    let printer = actor |x: i64| {
        println(x);
    };
    printer.send(42);
    printer.close();
}
